nncSdslStatistics.description: This module contains definitions for SDSL Ports Stats.

nncSdslLineStatusTable.name: nncSdslLineStatusTable
nncSdslLineStatusTable.description: Table that contains the Status of all SDSL Lines.

nncSdslLineStatusEntry.name: nncSdslLineStatusEntry
nncSdslLineStatusEntry.description: The Status of an SDSL Line.

nncSdslLineStatus.name: nncSdslLineStatus
nncSdslLineStatus.description: Status indicates current state of the line. Unknown 0 Operational 1 Near End Loss Of Cell Delineation 2 Near End Loss Of Signal 3 Near End Loss Of Power 34

nncSdslNearEndRawTable.name: nncSdslNearEndRawTable
nncSdslNearEndRawTable.description: Table that contains the Near End RAW Stats of all SDSL Ports.

nncSdslNearEndRawEntry.description: The Near End Raw Stats of an SDSL Port.

nncSdslNearEndRawLOS.name: nncSdslNearEndRawLOS
nncSdslNearEndRawLOS.description: Count of the number of Loss of Signal failures since system reset.

nncSdslNearEndRawLowNM.name: nncSdslNearEndRawLowNM
nncSdslNearEndRawLowNM.description: Count of the number of Low Noise Margin failures since system reset.

nncSdslNearEndRawLPR.name: nncSdslNearEndRawLPR
nncSdslNearEndRawLPR.description: Count of the number of Loss of Power failures since system reset.

nncSdslNearEndRawLOCD.name: nncSdslNearEndRawLOCD
nncSdslNearEndRawLOCD.description: Count of the number of Loss of Cell Delineation failures since system reset.

nncSdslNearEndRawCRCError.name: nncSdslNearEndRawCRCError
nncSdslNearEndRawCRCError.description: Count of the number of CRC Errors since system reset.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinTable.description: Table that contains the Near End 15 minutes current Stats of all SDSL Ports.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinEntry.description: The Near End 15 minutes current Stats of an SDSL Port.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval. A full interval is 900 seconds.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLOSS.name: nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLOSS
nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLOSS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Signal status not due to a Loss of Power in the current 15 minutes interval.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLOSWS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Synch Word status not followed by a Loss of Signal in the current 15 minutes interval.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLowNMS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Low Noise Margin status in the current 15 minutes interval.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinLPRS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Power status in the current 15 minutes interval.

nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinErrS.name: nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinErrS
nncSdslNearEndCurr15MinErrS.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the current 15 minutes interval. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more of the anomolies or defects previously defined.

nncSdslNearEndCurr1DayEntry.description: The Near End 1 Day current Stats of an SDSL Port.

nncSdslNearEndCurr1DayLOSWS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Synch Word status not followed by a Loss of Signal during the current day.

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayMoniSecs.name: nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayMoniSecs
nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayMoniSecs.description: The time in the PREVIOUS 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will normally be the same as the total interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring information can not be collected for any reason. Typically Elapsed 1-day Time will be copied into Monitored Seconds when the 1-day roll-over occurs.

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLOSS.name: nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLOSS
nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLOSS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Signal status not due to a Loss of Power within the most recent PREVIOUS 1 day period.

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLOSWS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Loss of Synch Word status not followed by a Loss of Signal within the most recent PREVIOUS 1 day period.

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLowNMS.description: Count of the number of seconds in Low Noise Margin status within the most recent PREVIOUS 1 day period.

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLPRS.name: nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayLPRS

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayErrS.name: nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayErrS

nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayValidData.name: nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayValidData
nncSdslNearEndPrev1DayValidData.description: This variable indicates if there is valid data for this interval.
